Sternlight) writes:

>One big omission in Phil's report, which I thought slanted the presentation,
>was a failure to focus on the voluntary nature of Clipper and on the White
>House statement about not banning non-Clipper crypto,  . . .

While the White House may have made a statement about not banning
non-Clipper cryptography, they certainly have not focused on its
voluntary nature, and therefore news reports that do not focus on it
either are accurately portraying the situation.


